---
layout: page.njk
title: Protractor
description: Turn a top-down radar photo into the cosine error angle used to correct measured speeds.
---

<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
  <section id="angle-tool-app" class="card angle-tool">
    <div id="angle-empty-state" class="angle-tool__empty-state">
      <div>
        <h2 class="angle-tool__title">Measure sensor angle</h2>
        <p class="angle-tool__lead">
          This tool turns a top-down photo into the cosine error angle used in
          Site Settings. Draw the kerb, draw the sensor beam, and it works out
          the number for you. That matters because the speed correction depends
          on this angle, and the computer will cheerfully do the wrong maths if
          you give it the wrong one.
        </p>
        <div class="angle-tool__actions">
          <label class="angle-tool__file-button" for="angle-file-input">
            Upload or take a photo
            <input id="angle-file-input" type="file" accept="image/*" hidden>
          </label>
          <a href="/guides/setup/#recording-your-mounting-angle" class="link">Back to the setup guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="angle-tool__sidecar">
        <h3 class="angle-tool__sidecar-title">What you are measuring</h3>
        <ul class="angle-tool__howto angle-tool__howto--bullets">
          <li>Take the photo straight down, perpendicular to the kerb, so the geometry is trustworthy.</li>
          <li>Draw the grey kerb line first. The tool derives the upright reference from that line automatically.</li>
          <li>Draw the emerald sensor beam second. The value below is the cosine error angle you enter in Site Settings.</li>
          <li>Aim for less than 30°. Lower angles need less correction, but the beam still has to cover the lane.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="angle-editor" class="angle-tool__editor hidden">
      <div id="angle-canvas-wrap" class="angle-tool__canvas-wrap">
        <canvas id="angle-canvas"></canvas>
        <div id="angle-hint" class="angle-tool__hint">Tap to place the kerb reference start</div>
      </div>

      <div class="angle-tool__readout" role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <div class="angle-tool__readout-row">
          <div class="angle-tool__readout-primary">
            <div class="angle-tool__readout-label">Cosine error angle</div>
            <div id="angle-align-value" class="angle-tool__readout-value">-</div>
          </div>

          <div class="angle-tool__readout-secondary">
            <div class="angle-tool__readout-label">Aim for</div>
            <div class="angle-tool__readout-value-small">Less than 30°</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="angle-tool__controls">
          <button id="angle-fit-btn" type="button" class="angle-tool__button">Fit view</button>
          <button id="angle-reset-btn" type="button" class="angle-tool__button">Reset lines</button>
          <button id="angle-download-btn" type="button" class="angle-tool__button angle-tool__button--accent">Download overlay</button>
          <label class="angle-tool__button" for="angle-file-input-2">
            New photo
            <input id="angle-file-input-2" type="file" accept="image/*" hidden>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</section>

<script src="/js/tool-protractor.js"></script>
